headline: Three Reasons to Avoid CLX and One Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Clorox has had an impressive run over the past six months as its shares have beaten the S&P 500 by 15%. The stock now trades at $168.49, marking a 27.9% gain. This was partly thanks to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
